               <msContents class="lemmatic">
                  <summary>This manuscript contains commentary on the book of Aphorisms attributed to <persName type="standard" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/287984736" key="person_287984736">Hippocrates</persName>.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_1632-item1">
                     <author key="person_4405945">
                        <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/4405945" type="aut">Ibn Abī Ṣādiq‏ابن أبي صادق</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_7754">Commentary on Hippocratic Aphorisms</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_7754">شرح فصول أبقراط</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="alt" key="work_7754">Sharḥ Fuṣūl Abuqrāṭ</title>
                     <note>Original manuscript in Süleymaniye Mosque.</note>
                     <note>This is a lemmatically arranged commentary. The introduction begins on <locus>f. 2b</locus>; the beginning of each Book is as follows: Bk1: 3b; Bk 2: 18a; Bk 3: 32b; Bk 4: 43a; Bk 5: 63b; Bk 6: 80b; Bk 7: 91a.</note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <persName type="standard" key="person_76527613" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/76527613">Ṣeṣen, Ramazan</persName>, <date calendar="#Gregorian" from="1984" to="1984">1984</date>, <biblScope unit="pages">p. 8</biblScope>
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc>
                        <extent n="105">105 leaves (ff. 1a-105b) <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm"/>
                        </extent>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="1" writtenLines="21">
                           <p>One column with 21 lines per page. The first hand rubricated the beginning of each lemma and the beginning of each commentary.</p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote scope="major" script="naskh" medium="ink">The text is written in naskh. <locus>Ff. 67b-68a</locus> are written by another hand; the paper, ink, pen nib, all change dramatically. <locus>Ff. 68b-69a</locus> appear to be taken from a different MS, being written on different paper, in a completely different hand (neat, tiny, naskh heavily influenced by nasta’liq). From <locus>f. 69b</locus>, the first hand returns to copy the text. Then the second hand completed <locus>ff. 82-105</locus>.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <p>Marginalia: The copy has been collated with the exemplar. The copyist has entered many corrections in the margins (frequently marked with صح).</p>
                  </additions>
               </physDesc>
               <history>
                  <origin change="#fix-dates">
                     <note>The copy was completed by two unnamed hands. The first hand completed the copy of ff. 1-81; the second hand completed ff. 82-105, and recorded the date of copying as <origDate notBefore="1324" notAfter="1325" calendar="#Hijri-qamari">Thursday, 9th of Shawwal, 725 AH</origDate> / <origDate calendar="#Gregorian" notBefore="1325" notAfter="1325">September 1325 CE</origDate>.</note>
                  </origin>
               </history>
